episodes.title: IndieFeed Performance Poetry, is now closed!
episodes.author: mongo@indiefeed.com (IndieFeed.com Community)
episodes.summary:
Dear Friends in the poetry community...

It's been an amazing decade:  1,614 shows.  632 poets.  Over 8 million downloads, and still counting...  But as of today, IndieFeed Performance Poetry has officially closed our doors, and we have ceased releasing new shows.

I want to send out a huge and warm thank you to everyone who has been involved with this project for the past decade:  Poets, hosts, listeners, donors, and supporters.  It's been an honor to work with all of you, and I look forward to future opportunities to share our love for the spoken word.

My main focus going forward will be The Performance Poetry Preservation Project (P4), and I invite you to join with me there in helping to preserve the legacy and the history of this vital cultural arts movement.  The entire archive of this podcast will soon become part of the P4 collection.  But until then, the Poets Index at the left is complete and up to date.  The IndieFeed archive constitutes more than 250 hours of poetry and commentary.  Please browse, share, and enjoy.

For IndieFeed, this is Mongo reminding you to Keep Reading, Keep Writing, Keep listening, and Keep Performing.  And we're signing out!

--Wess Mongo Jolley
  The IndieFeed Performance Poetry Channel

episodes.title: IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT: INDIEFEED PERFORMANCE POETRY WILL CEASE RELEASING NEW SHOWS.
episodes.author: mongo@indiefeed.com (IndieFeed.com Community)
episodes.summary:
Dear Loyal Listeners!

It's been a great ten year run, with more than 1600 poems, and more than 600 poets, but we're going to stop releasing new IndieFeed Performance Poetry shows, effective January 30, 2016.  Thank you to all of our poets, hosts, and listeners, for an amazing decade.  It's been a true pleasure and honor to have worked with all of you.  

And never fear, the catalog of IndieFeed shows will remain available.  We'll complete the poets index (to the left) once the show ends, and we'll keep it available until we move the content to a more permanent home.

Thanks again, and remember to keep reading, keep writing, keep listening, and keep recording!  

Wess Mongo Jolley
Founder and Channel Manager
The IndieFeed Performance Poetry Channel
